    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've built after thoroughly exploring the codebase:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: `@ai-sdk/pixelart` Provider\n\n**8 new files**, all inside `packages/pixelart/`:\n\n### Config / Build Files\n| File | Key Detail |\n|------|-----------|\n| `package.json` | `@ai-sdk/pixelart`, deps on `@ai-sdk/provider` + `@ai-sdk/provider-utils` (workspace), `zod` as peer dep |\n| `tsconfig.json` | Extends `@vercel/ai-tsconfig/ts-library.json`, `composite: true`, references `../provider` + `../provider-utils` |\n| `tsconfig.build.json` | Same as tsconfig.json but `composite: false` (required for tsup) |\n| `tsup.config.ts` | Single entry `src/index.ts`, outputs CJS + ESM + `.d.ts` |\n\n### Source Files\n| File | Key Detail |\n|------|-----------|\n| `src/pixelart-image-settings.ts` | `PixelArtImageModelId` union + `PixelArtImageSettings` interface (`size`, `style`, `pixelDensity`) |\n| `src/pixelart-image-model.ts` | `PixelArtImageModel` class implementing `ImageModelV3`; POSTs to `/images/generations`; issues warnings for unsupported `aspectRatio`, `seed`, `files`, `mask` |\n| `src/pixelart-provider.ts` | `createPixelArt()` factory, `PixelArtProvider` interface (image-only — no `ProviderV3`), `pixelart` default singleton; reads `PIXELART_API_KEY` env var |\n| `src/index.ts` | Barrel re-exports: `createPixelArt`, `pixelart` + all types |\n\n**Utilities reused** from `@ai-sdk/provider-utils`: `postJsonToApi`, `combineHeaders`, `createJsonResponseHandler`, `createJsonErrorResponseHandler`, `zodSchema`, `loadApiKey`, `withoutTrailingSlash`\n\n**Verification**: `pnpm type-check` (= `tsc --build`) from within `packages/pixelart/`",
